    {
      "label": "Further remarks",
      "value": "The handwriting points to an early date. The letters have been elongated Along the papyrus fibresly and large spaces have been left blank between the words. Initial kaf has a hairpin shape. The nun has a perfect semi-circular form. The letter sad and ta' have rectangular shape and have been elongated Along the papyrus fibresly.\nOn the basis of the handwriting should the letter on the verso be dated later than the letter on the recto"
    },
    {
      "label": "Content description",
      "value": "Verso: This is the end of a letter in which the sender conveys greetings to the addressee (l. 2). At the end of his letter the sender uses the same formula that was used to open letters in the first two Muslim centuries (l. 3)."
    },
    {
      "label": "Diacritical dots",
      "value": "There is one diacritical dot"
